# =========================================================
# Secrets — NEVER commit. Real values live in a secret
# manager / platform env (Vercel project settings), not here.
# Only .env.example (placeholders) is tracked. See README.md.
# =========================================================
.env
.env.*
*.env.local
!.env.example

# fnox: fnox.toml (ciphertext / provider refs) IS safe to commit and tracked.
# But the age decryption key and the resumable go-live ledger are NOT.
*.key
!fnox.toml.example
.mcp.json
!.mcp.json.example
.hamzaish-go-live.json

node_modules
.next
.vercel
.DS_Store
*.log
.turbo
coverage
.sentryclirc
test-results
playwright-report
playwright/.cache

# Auto-commit/push opt-out markers — operator-local discipline, never committed.
# /scaffold drops a .no-auto-push here so wip snapshots stay off the remote
# until you /ship. See docs/security.md (production-branch deploy model).
.no-auto-commit
.no-auto-push
.no-auto-pull

# Local-only Claude context & session notes — never committed, never public.
# START-HERE.local.md (generated by the factory) + CLAUDE.local.md + any *.local.md.
*.local.md

# Conversations / chat transcripts / strategy & discussion notes — NEVER commit.
# They belong in local memory (~/.claude/…), not in a product repo. Patterns end in
# .md/.txt so they can't shadow source files like Conversation.tsx (case-insensitive FS).
# Backstop only — the real guarantee is discipline. To truly track one: `git add -f`.
conversation.md
conversations.md
chat.md
chatlog.md
chat-log.md
transcript.md
transcripts.md
session-notes.md
strategy-notes.md
*.chat.md
*.conversation.md
*.transcript.md
*.transcript.txt
*.discussion.md
*.scratch.md
*-conversation.md
*-transcript.md
*-transcript.txt
*-chat-log.md
CONVERSATION.md
TRANSCRIPT.md
CHATLOG.md
DISCUSSION-NOTES.md

# /goal autonomy run logs (rubric, run journal) — local restore points.
.goal/

# Local Claude workspace: share project rules, commands & settings; ignore the rest
# (settings.local.json, the auto-generated .claude/HAMZAISH.md, etc.). settings.json
# is shared — it carries the fnox confinement deny-rules that MUST ship (see fnox.toml.example).
.claude/*
!.claude/rules
!.claude/commands
!.claude/settings.json

# Autonomy-loop control markers (see docs/autonomy.md) — operator-local.
.autonomy-ok
STOP

# Security-posture documents (audits, secret inventories, rotation logs, pentest
# findings) — NEVER commit these: they map your weaknesses even when they contain
# no keys. Keep them in meta/security/ locally or outside the repo entirely.
meta/security/
*SECURITY-AUDIT*
*security-audit*
*secrets-audit*
